label_values.value: FWIW, I think there are many words in English that follow this general pattern. Verb form is two words and noun form one word. Adjective form is the same as noun form, or sometimes hyphenated. Sometimes the "verb form" and "noun form" aren't really that connected, though (e.g. "stand by your man" vs. "i'm on standby").
